			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The fire pet should be reverted back to the warrior state it had pre-50. Ideally it should be something like this:
<br />

<br />
- same max melee hit as the water pet, no backstab of course.
<br />
- improved fire nuke, which should be strong enough so that (fire pet nuke damage = water pet nuke damage + water pet backstab damage) over time.
<br />
- fire elemental aura (or upgrade).
<br />
- low hitpoints (comparable to water)
<br />

<br />

<br />
Reasoning for this pet:
<br />
- pets need to be sources of sustained damage. A wizard pet that relies on a mana pool (which means, it can run OOM) CANNOT fill this role.
<br />
- we have two tank pets: air and earth, but only one damage pet, water. Fire should take the role of the second damage pet. It should NOT become a tanking pet.
<br />
- while the fire elemental aura would not be needed (since the pet is not intended to tank), it has always been part of the fire pets, so why should it not be anymore?
<br />
- a warrior type fire pet would be much easier to improve through focus items than a caster pet.
<br />
- we have a pet that can do great damage from all directions: the epic pet. However it is limited in its usefulness because of its low level. It is time that we get such a general purpose damage pet again, and the fire pet could take that role.
<br />

<br />

<br />
If the devs are adamant on keeping the wizard pet however, I would prefer if they upgrade our current fire pets in the following way:
<br />

<br />
- remove root/dispel/ae's from the spell lineup
<br />
- base pet mana regen on the pet focus items: mana regen should be as fast as hitpoint regen for a focused pet. Or even better, give them an unlimited mana pool (see my reasoning above!)
<br />
- increase the melee to match that of the other pets if you keep the mana pool: the pet MUST be able to do damage even when it runs OOM.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 67 Arch Convoker on Quellious (semi retired)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
