				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First, there are occasions where a casting only pet are needed over a melee pet.  Mobs that can only be melee hit by a bane weapon anyone ?
<br />

<br />
To fix the fire pet I would like to see the following.
<br />

<br />
* Remove the AoE spells and dispells from lineup.
<br />

<br />
* Add 2 command to the game.   /pet melee (on/off)  
<br />
                                                /pet cast (on/off)
<br />

<br />
this will benefit the Mage class MUCH MUCH more than a single pet fix.  Pet melee (off) could be used with  1.Earth pet and it would only cast root on target (there is the root spell we always wanted).   2.Air pet would become a stun caster that would be useful against mobs who try to gate at low health(can you say group friendly ??).  Water, well it casts cold base spell.
<br />

<br />
But anyway you get the picture.   As far as mana regen now that pets can be buffed just hit em with VoQ and be done with it.  Make it a wizard and you have to tell pet to sit to increase mana regen.  Telling it to sit would be fine with me if we got the benefits of a pure cast ,pure melee, or both optioned pet.
<br />

<br />
Wilee<br />_________________<br />Wilee Castusmaximas
