			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Crossposted from another thread (that is not as old as this one)
<br />

<br />
I would love to see the fire pet changed to a pet that roots itself when attacking (so you can park it somewhere) and it will only cast a very small selection of pet specific spells... 
<br />

<br />
I mean, give it 1 cold DD for 150, 1 Fire DD for 150 and 1 Magic DD for 150. 
<br />
Let the pet switch to another nuke when it gets a resist (someone else wrote this before on how the pet should switch his spells etc). 
<br />
Advantage of this is that it is easily balancable and also very easily upgradable through focusitems (make the focus give it 10% more damage for instance, or 20% or whatever). It will also give us some DPS against fire and magic resistant mobs. And most important, the pet DPS should stay about the same no matter what mob you fight. 
<br />

<br />
Another advantage of "small nukes" is that the pet can cast very quickly after going OOM. It will not drop in DPS for a long time, although going OOM will drop it's effectiveness.. but with Pet Affinity and KEI as well as Kindle it should be able to stay nuking for at least a minute or 2 (with KEI, Kindle, Pot9, SD etc on it, make it shorter when those buffs are not on it, specially now that we have zoning pets) 
<br />

<br />
I think this pet should be about 10% better in DPS then our normall pets (assuming those get upgraded a bit cause, from what i understand, that is the part our pets lack in in high end stuff). It might even be an option to give it 20 or even 30% more and make that our DPS pet for trinity groups and raids. 
<br />

<br />
i would prefer 10% for DPoC, 15% for next level till 30% for the current top line pet focus. That way the fire pet would be the first well scaled pet with focusses (since it doesn't melee it's a bit easier to balance) 
<br />

<br />
What i would hope is that our DD bracer and mana pres earring would help the petas well (another 20% (would this be too much or give balancing trouble?) and also mana pres... damn, more firepet nukage <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />)
<br />

<br />
PS: Amount of damage as well as mana cost are all examples (i didn't care to do the math), balancing of the pet should give us what we want/need a long range damage pet that will be nice in groups AND raids. Of course this pet would suck goatballs through a garden hose when soloing<br />_________________<br />In the end everything is okay.
<br />
If it's not okay it's not the end.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29332">Oliadar</a>, Level 65 Erudite Arch Mage
