				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would change it to one of these three:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">1) Build a Better Wizard</span> - Remove root, dispell, buffs, and AE's from spell lineup.  Increase natural mana regen, or increase mana regen given by Kindle.  Remove the pet's melee ability.  Code the pet to stay next to its master at all times, and to /pet sit down when it is low on mana.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">2) Old School Fire Pet</span> - Make all 50+ fire pets into cookie-cutter versions of their pre-50 selves.  High chance of self-DS, moderate HP's, moderate melee ability, good damage Fire DD proc.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">3) Zobober the Zerker</span> - Change the fire pet's class to Berserker.  Add kick and frenzy (added 1-3 attacks outside of regular melee) to its combat abilities.  Also procs a Fire DD that does the same damage as water pet's Cold DD.  Chance to cast FireElementalAura increased to what it was pre-50.  HP's will be same as water pet, max damage will be same as air pet.  This pet will replace the water pet in cases where you cannot position your pet correctly for maximum DPS.  Compared to a water pet that is positioned correctly at all times, this pet will have slightly lower sustained and nearly equal burst DPS.
<br />

<br />
In a poll of over 50 mages (found <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=15828" target="_blank" class="postlink">here</a>), 75% preferred "Build a Better Wizard"<br />_________________<br />--<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=559376" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arc</a>--
<br />
62nd level Arch Mage
<br />
