				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If the devs can not or will not make it a "smart" wizard that never goes oom, does not cast roots/dispells/AE's then I like the idea above of making it into its old warrior self with melee = water and an innate PROC that will = the BS+Proc of the water with the innate DS. Maybe even add the ability to DS the Mages whole group with FireElemenatalAura. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Considering the fact that I don't think the dev or wizzy would like us to have an infinite mana always nuking leashed mini wizzy (and it might be a tad overpowered unless he chain cast level 16 spells), and the fact that 75% of the people in the poll yet have said they want a "fixed" wizzy pet, here's what I propose. 
<br />

<br />
-Put his melee damage back to other pets level. He has lower atk, offense, defense, etc than other pets anyway so will only be a small boost. NPC wizzies don't hit for less than another mob of their level, they just hit less often for max, pet wizzy should be the same. 
<br />

<br />
-like was mentioned by pretty much everyone, remove dispells, AoEs and root from his spell line-up. Those spells are VERY annoying when cast randomly by weak AI. Annoying to the point that I have not used a single fire pet since level 49, beside toying around lvl 20 mobs. At least they removed gate from line-up back in kunark (so don't tell me it can't be done, first generation wizzy pets GATED when they were low on hp, to the spot where you summoned them, and yes, pets were still aggro at that time too, was kinda funny in a very sadistic way, prolly was done on purpose!).
<br />

<br />
These two changes alone would make a good enough fire pet imho. He would be a dps pet, and his dps would fluctuate with his mana pool. If he had enough mana to nuke a lot in a fight, he would be over water pet, out of mana, he would be the worst dps pet. That would situationally make him a replacement for water pet. Constant pulls water would do better, fire would be worst, slow pulls heavy dps fight fire would be the best. It's simple to put in, very "balanced" (/wave to the vision) and I think would make some people actualy use 50 + fire pets in some situations.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721" target="_blank" class="postlink">Woon</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
