				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Woon,
<br />

<br />
If you read the description of "Build a Better Wizard," it says that the fire pet's melee ability would be completely removed, in favor of higher mana regen.  What this would essentially mean is that the pet would act alot like a regular caster in a battle.  If the battle is short, the pet would be a huge source of burst DPS throughout the whole battle.  However, if the battle is long, the pet will eventually run OOM and have to regen the mana back, slowing down how often it casts spells.  This would reduce its DPS substantially.  So basically, with this fix, the fire pet = best burst DPS, the water pet = best sustained DPS, which is exactly how wizards and rogues are right now.  I don't see wizards running in and whacking the mob when they go OOM.<br />_________________<br />--<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=559376" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arc</a>--
