			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I like having pets that are *different*.  I'm sure most of you guys/gals do too.  I personally always liked to think of the air pet as a monk, though nowadays he's more like a warrior with a 2 liter of Jolt in him.  I think a compromise in favor of wizard pet is in order.  Basically the fire pet, imho, breaks down into 3 parts.
<br />

<br />
1. Damage Shield - I always liked the fact that I didn't have to DS the fire pet.  Honestly I do not think a FireElementalAura would be overpowering.  Even with Qvic focus that would be a... 66pt DS?  Maybe a daggerless rogue with overhaste is shaking in his boots, but mobs who hit for 500 aren't really impressed.  Also, I think the O'Kiels should stay.  Lastly, add an item with effect: Flameshield on it, that way even chaincasting he'll still have a decent inherent DS.  With prep-time, he could hit as high as 48+62+8 = 118 pt DS, which might actually be useful.
<br />

<br />
2. Nukes/Pseudo-Proc - Drop the 'same as water pet fire spell every 6 seconds' idea.  If you really feel so strongly, add in a 140pt FR DD proc.  The DPS increase would be neglible, but there would be pretty sparkleys, which we all must confess to enjoying.  I personally prefer bigger booms rather than a steady supply of smaller (i.e. Servant of Ro) because the fire pet would supercede water except on mobs where melee is all that will hit.  A mana regen increase is definitely in order, scalar with focus and also a boosted kindle.  I'd pay 350 mana for a caster version of burnout.  Maybe another spell that lets us mana dump the pet for those mobs that have huge FR/MR.  So far, the selfroot component is the best idea I've heard that would be simple to code.  Pie in the sky:  reworked pet caster AI/selectable spell lineup.
<br />

<br />
3. Melee Characteristics - Lower maxhit is fine.  It doesn't make much difference, as the pet should not be meleeing much if at all *anyway*.  It must be remembered though, that in the end, the fire pet IS an elemental, not a robe wearing weenie.  Some mild meleeing ability is in order, possibly slightly higher HP than air with better mitigation and virtually nonexistant avoidance; to take advantage of the (118pt?) damage shield.  It doesn't need to be able to hold its own against an XP mob, just needs to last long enough for me to flee or get a tank pet up.<br />_________________<br />Dorai Darkspire, 65 Arch Convoker of Maelin Starpyre
<br />
<a  href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=12792">MC0.8 MAG65.71 /MS Rh 2.4khp 4.4kmp ft8 r6 !G e+(++) p D+ o+ T++ L !H f+ !b(b-) t+ Dm !X(X----)</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
