			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I believe the fire pet should be a viable, ranged DPS pet that does the majority of its damage through nukes rather than melee.
<br />

<br />
The easiest way to implement this that I see, is to completely remove any melee abilities from the pet and have it simply chain cast a single, fire-based (it is a fire pet right?) nuke.  Preferably, that nuke should have a good resist modifier to it so that it consistently does a significant amount of damage.  Something in the range of 600 damage per cast, 5 second casting time (2.25 recycle time) would be about right, putting the DPS output of the pet around 80 DPS.  This is lower than the water pet, but it should be since it does not require positioning (beyond getting it in range).  Different foci (DPoC, GoDS, etc. etc.) can increase the damage that the spell does (e.g. DPoC fire pet nukes for 610 rather than 600...  SoAS might bring it up to 650).
<br />

<br />
Give the pet mana, but change kindle so that the pet can continuously nuke while kindle is active.  Thus, comparable to having to cast burnout on our melee pets to ensure their maximal DPS, we'd have to cast kindle on our fire pet to keep it going.
<br />

<br />
Belthil.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">EDIT:  I just thought I would add some of my reasoning behind this suggestion.  The guild I am in has recently started killing the Emperor Ssraeshza.  For those that are unaware, he's completely immune to melee damage unless you have a bane weapon equipped, and thus would appear to be the quintessential example of when to use the fire pet.  While my calculations aren't complete yet, it appears that the innate proc from the Servant of Marr actually out-damages Child of Ro on the emperor.  Why is this?  Because Child of Ro spends his time casting MR based spells that get completely resisted rather than sticking to cold/fire based nukes.
<br />

<br />
One of the biggest problems with the existing fire pet is its irregular spell usage.  It is difficult to predict exactly when it will try casting dispell, root, snare, stuns, or just straight nukes (and even then, magic, cold or fire?).  Thus my suggestion that any 'upgraded' fire pet be limited to a single nuke.  Does this mean it would be completely useless against a 100% FR mob?  Yes.  But I would rather have a pet that is useful in 90% of situations while useless in 10% than have a half-assed pet that's effectively useless 100% of the time.
<br />

<br />
As far as where the fire pet should fit in the DPS scale of things, I think it needs to be between the air and water pets.  We currently have 2 'tanking' pets, with variations in their characteristics (stun vs root, hps vs avoidance) that make one or the other better depending on the situation.  I would like to see the same thing with 2 options for 'DPS' pets.  Currently we have Servant of Marr.  SoM is higher DPS than the air pet (even from the front due to its proc), but to get maximal damage output it needs to be properly positioned behind the mob.  A fire pet that strictly nukes would be much easier to use.  Thus it would have to put out less DPS than the water pet or we'll just be in the situation of replacing the water pet and we'll end up complaining that SoM never gets used.</span><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597105" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Belthil Telperion</a>
<br />
65 Magician, Erollisi Marr</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
